---
title: What Will Your Group Do This Weekend?
description: Talk about group routine plans using future simple conjugations
level: elementary
time: 20 minutes
---

# Grammar: Future Simple for Routine Plans

## Build a Future Routine Plan

Use the infinitive + future endings (-e, -as, -a, -emos, -an) for planned actions.

Este sabado nos levantaremos temprano.
  This Saturday we will get up early.

Despues desayunaremos y ellos trabajaran.
  After that we will have breakfast and they will work.

Luego ellas haran ejercicio y nosotros almorzaremos.
  Then they will exercise and we will have lunch.

Por la noche cenaremos, veremos la tele y dormiremos.
  At night we will have dinner, watch TV, and sleep.

## Invitation Pattern

Use this to invite someone into your plan.

Querras + infinitive?
  Will you want to + verb?

Querras cenar con nosotros?
  Will you want to have dinner with us?

# Conjugation: trabajar (to work)
tense: Future Simple
type: regular -ar
yo -> trabajare [trah-bah-hah-REH]
tu -> trabajaras [trah-bah-hah-RAHS]
el/ella/usted -> trabajara [trah-bah-hah-RAH]
nosotros -> trabajaremos [trah-bah-hah-REH-mohs]
ellos/ellas/ustedes -> trabajaran [trah-bah-hah-RAHN]

# Conjugation: hacer (to do)
tense: Future Simple
type: irregular stem (har-)
yo -> hare [ah-REH]
tu -> haras [ah-RAHS]
el/ella/usted -> hara [ah-RAH]
nosotros -> haremos [ah-REH-mohs]
ellos/ellas/ustedes -> haran [ah-RAHN]

# Vocabulary: Routine Verbs (Weekend Plan)

levantarse
  to get up
  [leh-bahn-TAHR-seh]

desayunar
  to have breakfast
  [deh-sah-yoo-NAHR]

trabajar
  to work
  [trah-bah-HAHR]

hacer ejercicio
  to exercise
  [ah-SEHR ehk-hehr-SEE-see-oh]

almorzar
  to have lunch
  [ahl-mohr-SAHR]

cenar
  to have dinner
  [seh-NAHR]

ver la tele
  to watch TV
  [behr lah TEH-leh]

dormir
  to sleep
  [dohr-MEER]

# Vocabulary: Time Expressions for Plans

este fin de semana
  this weekend
  [EHS-teh feen deh seh-MAH-nah]

el sabado
  on Saturday
  [ehl SAH-bah-doh]

el domingo
  on Sunday
  [ehl doh-MEEN-goh]

por la manana
  in the morning
  [pohr lah mah-NYAH-nah]

al mediodia
  at noon
  [ahl meh-dee-oh-DEE-ah]

por la tarde
  in the afternoon
  [pohr lah TAHR-deh]

por la noche
  at night
  [pohr lah NOH-cheh]

# Vocabulary: Street Weekend Talk (Northern Mexico)

el plan
  the plan
  [ehl plahn]

la chamba
  work / the job (casual)
  [lah CHAHM-bah]

Que plan traeran para el sabado?
  What will your group plan be for Saturday?
  [keh plahn trah-EHR-ahn pah-rah ehl SAH-bah-doh]

Nos levantaremos, iremos a la chamba y luego haremos ejercicio.
  We will get up, go to work, and then exercise.
  [nohs leh-bahn-tah-REH-mohs ee-REH-mohs ah lah CHAHM-bah ee LWEH-goh ah-REH-mohs ehk-hehr-SEE-see-oh]

Ellos caeran en la tarde y yo pondre la cena.
  They will show up in the afternoon and I will make dinner.
  [EH-yohs kah-eh-RAHN ehn lah TAHR-deh ee yoh pohn-DREH lah SEH-nah]

En la noche veremos la tele un rato y luego dormiremos.
  At night we will watch TV for a bit and then sleep.
  [ehn lah NOH-cheh beh-REH-mohs lah TEH-leh oon RRAH-toh ee LWEH-goh dohr-mee-REH-mohs]

# Phrases: Planning the Routine

Que haran este fin de semana?
  What will you all do this weekend?
  [keh ah-RAHN EHS-teh feen deh seh-MAH-nah]

Nos levantaremos temprano y desayunaremos juntos.
  We will get up early and have breakfast together.
  [nohs leh-bahn-tah-REH-mohs tehm-PRAH-noh ee deh-sah-yoo-nah-REH-mohs HOON-tohs]

Despues ellos trabajaran y ellas haran ejercicio.
  After that they will work and they will exercise.
  [dehs-PWEHS EH-yohs trah-bah-hah-RAHN ee EH-yahs ah-RAHN ehk-hehr-SEE-see-oh]

Luego almorzaremos, cenaremos, veremos la tele y dormiremos.
  Then we will have lunch, have dinner, watch TV, and sleep.
  [LWEH-goh ahl-mohr-sah-REH-mohs seh-nah-REH-mohs beh-REH-mohs lah TEH-leh ee dohr-mee-REH-mohs]

Yo llevare postre para todos.
  I will bring dessert for everyone.
  [yoh yeh-bah-REH pohs-TREH pah-rah TOH-dohs]

